# BIO410-Final-Project
## Background
The data consist of 6 samples from the Zaire Ebolavirus. This organism is a type of virus that is invloved in causing fatal hemorrhagic fever in humans and mammals [https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37355146/]. 

## Purpose
The purpose of this project was to creat a phylogenetic tree from 6 sample of Ebolavirus, in order to determine the evolutionary relationship between the samples.

## Methods
-The sequencing reads reads came from Next Gen Seq
- Assembled the sequence using MEGAHIT
- Aligneed the sequence using a package DECIPHER 
- Then created a phylogenetic tress using ML method in R package DECIPHER
